<s> [INST] You are an expert in Natural Language Inference (NLI). Please list all possible explanations why the the following statement is false (contradiction) given the context below without introductory phrases. 
Context: He found himself thinking in circles of worry and pulled himself back to his problem. 
Statement: He could not afford to get distracted from his problem. 
Answer: [/INST] 1. He was not worried about his problem, hence not thinking in circles of worry.
2. He was not pulled back to his problem, indicating a lack of effort to refocus.
3. He was able to afford distractions, implying financial ability to be sidetracked.
4. His distraction was not related to his problem, thus not affecting his ability to solve it.
5. His distraction was beneficial to his problem-solving process.
6. His distraction was unavoidable or necessary, and therefore not something he could afford to prevent.</s>